latest_release.name: Version 2.0.0
latest_release.body:
- Add `sudo -E` flag on `docker-php-ext-install` in CircleCI [[#33](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/33)]
- Add `--create-target-dir` flag [[#31](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/31)]
- Ignore log files [[#29](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/29)]
- Move command over to new v2 structure [[#27](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/27)]
- Update `circle.yml` to use its v2 API [[#25](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/25)]
- Add MIT license to the project [[#24](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/24)]
- Regenerate README to include Circle badge [[#21](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/21)]
- Properly ignore `.DS_Store` in the top-level directory and subdirs [[#20](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/20)]
- Abstract `dist-archive` to `Dist_Archive_Command` [[#19](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/19)]
- Update package tests and README for the move [[#18](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/18)]
- Rename package to wp-cli/dist-archive-command [[#17](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/17)]
- Include the current hash in archives when version includes `-alpha` [[#14](https://api.github.com/repos/wp-cli/dist-archive-command/issues/14)]
